            android:text="Prepare the Pork Belly:

Cut the pork belly into serving pieces, making sure the skin is intact.
Boil the Pork:

In a large pot, place the pork belly pieces, sliced onion, minced garlic, bay leaves, peppercorns, and salt.
Add enough water to cover the pork belly.
Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to simmer. Cook until the pork is tender, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Drain and Air-Dry:

Remove the pork belly from the pot and drain excess water. Let it air-dry for at least 30 minutes or pat it dry with paper towels.
Heat Oil for Frying:

In a deep pan or pot, heat cooking oil over medium-high heat.
Deep Fry:

Carefully lower the pork belly pieces into the hot oil. Fry until the skin becomes crispy and golden brown.
Drain Excess Oil:

Remove the pork belly from the oil and drain on paper towels to remove excess oil.
Slice and Serve:

Let the pork belly rest for a few minutes, then slice into serving pieces.
Serve hot with your favorite dipping sauce or with a side of steamed rice."
